      "review_summary": "The PR adds a Mattermost `inferTargetChatType` hook, moves shared target inference to consult plugin hooks before the generic `channel:` fallback, and uses a monitor-populated Mattermost channel-kind cache during session-route resolution.\n\nPR surface: Source +61. Total +61 across 5 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for source-level reproduction: current main maps Mattermost private-channel type `P` to `group`, while outbound target/session routing can still derive or store the same `channel:<id>` destination as `channel`. I did not run a live Mattermost workspace.",
