        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(mattermost): implement inferTargetChatType hook to resolve private channel chat_type",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nMattermost private channels (type `P`) are authoritatively typed as `group` by `mapMattermostChannelTypeToChatType`, but are addressed as `channel:<id>` — the same prefix as public channels. The generic `inferChatTypeFromTarget` in `targets.ts` matched the `channel:` prefix and returned `\"channel\"` before the plugin hook could override it. This caused the same conversation to be keyed under two different session namespaces (`group:<id>` inbound vs `channel:<id>` delivery), splitting thread delivery across incompatible session keys.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nTwo fixes work together:\n\n1. **`src/infra/outbound/targets.ts`**: Reordered `inferChatTypeFromTarget` to consult the plugin `inferTargetChatType` hook BEFORE the `channel:`/`thread:` prefix default. Previously the prefix match short-circuited and the hook was never reached for `channel:` targets. Now plugins can override the chat type for ambiguous prefixes. The unambiguous `user:` and `group:` prefixes are still checked first.\n\n2. **`extensions/mattermost/`**: Implemented Mattermost missing `inferTargetChatType` hook (Telegram, Discord, Signal, iMessage, Slack, ClickClack, WhatsApp all already implement it). The hook resolves `user:`→direct, `group:`→group, and `channel:<id>` via a module-level cache populated by the monitor when channel info is fetched through the existing `resolveChannelInfo` path. Also fixed `resolveMattermostOutboundSessionRoute` to propagate `\"group\"` chatType when `resolvedTarget.kind === \"group\"`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/infra/outbound/targets.ts`** — reorder `inferChatTypeFromTarget`: plugin hook before `channel:`/`thread:` default\n- **`extensions/mattermost/src/channel.ts`** — add `inferTargetChatType` hook consulting cache\n- **`extensions/mattermost/src/session-route.ts`** — propagate `group` chatType from resolvedTarget\n- **`extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor-gating.ts`** — add module-level `mattermostChannelKindCache` + `setMattermostChannelKindCache`\n- **`extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor-resources.ts`** — populate channel kind cache in `resolveChannelInfo`\n- **`extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.ts`** — add import for future cache use\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Design verification\n\nThe `inferTargetChatType` hook pattern is already implemented by 7 other channel plugins. Tested approaches in existing plugins:\n\n- **Telegram** (`channel.ts:812`): `inferTargetChatType: ({ to }) => resolveTelegramRouteTarget(to).chatType` — carries chatType on route target\n- **Discord** (`channel.ts:338`): `inferTargetChatType: ({ to }) => parseDiscordTarget(to, { defaultKind: \"channel\" })?.kind`\n- **Signal** (`channel.ts:304`): `inferTargetChatType: ({ to }) => inferSignalTargetChatType(to)`\n\nThe Mattermost implementation follows the same established pattern, with a module-level cache for the channel-type resolution that the prefix-based target string cannot encode.\n\n### Existing test coverage\n\nThe Mattermost plugin has existing tests for `mapMattermostChannelTypeToChatType` in:\n- `extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor-gating.test.ts`\n- `extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.channel-kind.test.ts`\n\nThe targets module has existing tests exercising `inferTargetChatType` in:\n- `src/infra/outbound/targets.test.ts`\n\n## Related\n\nCloses #95646",
